Cookies

-a way to track you
-server gives each browser a unique cookie
-the unique cookie will be the key to the key/value pair
-possible to store info to cookies, but its just an identifier
- used to dentify the user and retrieve ther session data on request

Session

-server side that completes the cookies
-the info we want to track from our user
-sessions

Purpose

-user does not have to enter info every time
-personalization of a website
-tracks a users identity
    -pages visited, links clicked (marketing)

Real world example

-adding an item to the cart is just cookies and sessions
-nike made it so that even if you close the browser the cookie keeps your items in the cart

key/value pairs

Session Tracking w Java
-using the built in functionality sessions in this course
-wont interact w cookies directly
-interacting w a session object that is provided with the servlet library
-w Java Servlets it automatically uses cookies to track for each browser

Working w Sessions Examples
language exmaple:
doPost {

//get session object from the request
HttpSession session = request.getSession();

//Set a session attribute to store users lang pref
session.setAttribute("language", "en-us");

//retrieve the session attribute to determine the users lang
String languagePreferences = (String) session.getAttribute("language");

//use the lan pref to render the page content
if (languagePreference.equals("en-us")) {
//render content in english
} else if (languagePreference.equals("fr-fr")) {
//render content in french
} else {
//render page content in default lang
}

}



user and pass example:

doPost {

//get session username and pass from the request parameters
String username = request.getParameter("username");
String pass = request.getParameter("pass");

//validate user and pass
if (username.equals("admin") && pass.equals("pass")) {
//if valid, create a session
Httpsession session = request.getSession();
session.setAttribute("username", username);
//redirect to welcome page
response.sendRedirect("WelcomeServlet");

}  else {
//if not valid show error message
}

}



